  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level of 3 due to the single-configuration ASTM F1717 protocol; this shortfall is mitigated by inter-laboratory replication (N=11, two independent facilities) and the consistently low E/uval values (maximum 1.12) across all QoIs. Model risk level 3 (Medium) is consistent with the Medium assurance level and Medium model influence and decision consequence ratings. The FEA framework is judged credible for the stated COU. Decision: Accepted with the condition that additional loading configurations be evaluated in the next design iteration.",
